class.name: Pyrroles

subclass.name: Substituted pyrroles
subclass.description: Heterocyclic compounds containing a pyrrole ring substituted at one or more positions.

direct_parent.name: Phenylpyrroles
direct_parent.description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing a benzene ring linked to a pyrrole ring through a CC or CN bond.

alternative_parents.name: Triazolopyrimidines
alternative_parents.description: Polycyclic aromatic compounds containing triazole ring fused to a pyrimidine ring. Triazole is a five-membered ring consisting of two carbon atoms and three nitrogen atoms. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.

alternative_parents.name: Pyrrolopyrimidines
alternative_parents.description: Compounds containing a pyrrolopyrimidine moiety, which consists of a pyrrole ring fused to a pyrimidine. Pyrrole is 5-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and one nitrogen atom. Pyrimidine is a 6-membered ring consisting of four carbon atoms and two nitrogen centers at the 1- and 3- ring positions.
